body, html 
	padding 0
	margin 0
	background-color backgroundGrey
	font-smoothing antialiased !important
	
* 
	box-sizing border-box

/* 
There's a bit of magic happening here with the `section` element.

We're using custom HTML elements (Yep, they're valid HTML5) and custom
elements need to have their display property set. Typically, you'll 
want them to be display block. And since we're making liberal use of the
section tag, we may as well assume that the first child of <section> should 
have it's display property set to `block`

In addition, we're using a different clear fix to the one Jeet reccomends.
*/
section
	> *
		display block
		center()
	&:after
		content:"";
		display:table;
		clear:both;

	
